<h3 class="para">Quality, Safety and Environmental Management Policy</h3>
<div class="paragraph" >
    <p><b>A. Quality, Safety and Environmental Management Policy</b></p>
    <p>
         NII concerns to improve quality service to fulfill customer satisfaction.
         Our value is customer satisfaction create our high performance & productive company.
         NII consistently implements Quality Management System Standards (ISO 9001:2000).
         NII Quality Policy is Smart and Reliability Shipping Company.
         Smart shipping company to provide service with reliable resources.
    </p>
    <p>
        NII operates a sea transportation service and effectively and consistently applies its 
        Safety Management System and Environmental Protection (SMSEP) as a commitment and guarantee 
        that NII's quality ensures that it is capable of operating its ships and emphasizing 
        shipboard safety; the safety of life, the prevention of accidents and the prevention of environmental pollution; 
        and by applying such safety standards with discipline and seriousness.
    </p>
    <p> 
        NII has laid down its SMSEP in accordance with the International Safety Management Code (ISM Code) in order that
        it may operate its fleets safely and securely while safeguarding environmental pollution prevention. 
        Its SMSEP System is laid down in its guidance manuals and has been implemented in all working units,
        both in the offices of NII and its ships.
    </p>
    <p>
        NII takes full responsibility for applying the SMSEP and guarantees that the personnel involved in it, both on land and onboard ships have been trained and educated to carry out their work, in accordance with their responsibilities and authority, and always in compliance with the SMSEP Policy's procedures.
    </p>
    <p>
        NII has appointed a Designated Person Ashore (DPA) to whom it entrusts the responsibility and authority to monitor and maintain the SMSEP Policy. The DPA will maintain the integrity of the SMSEP Policy's directives.
    </p>
    <p>
        NII SMSEP Policy is binding. All working units (office and ship) and human resources of NII are obliged to obey this directive and are responsible for implementing the policy to the full.
    </p>
    <p>
        Specifically for waste oil pollution handling, NII has been strictly bounded by Shipboard Oil Pollution Emergency Plan (SOPEP) regulation and procedure that is endorsed by Seacom (Sea Communication) as administrator for Vietnamese vessels.
    </p>

    <p><b>B. Specific Policies</b></p>
