          </a>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-body collapse in">
          <div class="accordion-inner">
            <p>
                Technical support and back-up to ensure that our Fleet is running well is provided by NII's technical (fleet) division in Ho Chi Minh City under its Fleet Director. Each vessel will be assigned to a Fleet Manager and his superintendent.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-group">
        <div class="accordion-heading">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" >
            B.3. Maintenance and Repair 
          </a>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-body collapse in">
          <div class="accordion-inner">
            <p>
                Maintenance of the vessel, its hull and equipment will be in accordance with customary seaman-like practices as outlined in the company's procedure manuals, extracts from which are appended to this statement.
            </p>
            <p>
                The vessel's machinery is be maintained strictly in accordance with makers' guidelines and schedules. Routine day to day maintenance will be carried out by ship's crew without delay to the ship. Periodic maintenance / overhaul will, in the first place be scheduled for the one-day-per month maintenance allowance, always in coordination with Charterers. NII superintendents will be available to attend overhauls and carry out routine inspections as often as are required, and assistance from maker's service engineers will be available.
            </p>
            <p>
                Main engine makers recommend a thorough engine overhaul after 4,000 running hours and major overhauls after 10,000 hours - which translate into dry dock requirement around every 18 months and 41 months.
            </p>
            <p>
                It is intended that such major overhauls be carried out, under the supervision of service representatives, before the vessel enters Charterers' service. Class and flag surveys and certification will similarly be brought up to date during this pre-service overhaul period. In consultation with the client we will determine the voyage and dry dock planning.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
