            <p>
                NII has already implemented a "quality, safety and environmental protection system" throughout its fleet.
            </p>
            <p><b> Environmental Protection </b><br />
                Owners' environmental protection plan is incorporated within its safety and environmental protection system and addresses water and air pollution prevention. Specifically for waste oil pollution handling, NII has been strictly controlled by the Shipboard Oil Pollution Emergency Plan (SOPEP) regulations and procedures that are endorsed by Seacom (Sea Communication Department of the Vietnam Government). 
            </p>
            <p><b>Safety and Loss Control Program </b><br />
                Safety, loss prevention, health, and training programs are incorporated within the ISM safety systems. These programs will be adapted to suit the Client's operations and to meet the Client's requirements and training programs. 
            </p>
            <p><b>Safety Representation / Reporting Requirements / Reviews</b><br />
                
                NII has delegated personnel who are responsible for the supervision and review of safety and environmental matters including the reporting and review of any accidents or injuries and be fully available to liaise with Clients and attend meetings as required.
            </p>
